[{"question":"What -- what\u0027s been going on there?","answer":".","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":22,"aSentId":23},{"question":"What do you say to the skeptics?","answer":"Well, charity should begin at home and there\u0027s a tremendous amount of work being done and certainly we have to pay attention to -- you know, we haven\u0027t really dealt with Katrina.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":78,"aSentId":79},{"question":"How much emotional energy are you expending on this?","answer":"I spend, you know, hours a day on it.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":90,"aSentId":91},{"question":"Why does this cause mean so much to you?","answer":"I have to say, you have a very nice tie and I know you -- you could be George.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"How -- how close have you come to getting hurt?","answer":"You know, not really.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"Have you discovered that you\u0027re braver than you may have thought you were?","answer":"No.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":134,"aSentId":135},{"question":"As a father, do you worry about George when he goes off on these crusades there?","answer":"The answer to that question is yes.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":159,"aSentId":160},{"question":"Why -- why are you constantly fighting this kind of uphill struggle?","answer":"I think -- I think a lot of times and I think most newsmen would agree, my father being one of them, that it\u0027s not just necessarily hard news sell the Sudan, it\u0027s a hard news sell virtual -- many, many of the hot spots around the world that it\u0027s, you know, it\u0027s hard to get Burma on the news.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":170,"aSentId":171},{"question":"Nick, as George\u0027s father again, do you get incensed on his behalf?","answer":"You bet.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":197,"aSentId":198},{"question":"And do you -- do you use maybe juicier language than that?","answer":"Almost never.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":203,"aSentId":204},{"question":"George, do you -- do you believe there\u0027s going to be peace in Sudan in the next few years or are you quite pessimistic about that?","answer":"No.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":244,"aSentId":245},{"question":"Are you worried for your own personal safety that the more high-profile you get?","answer":"No.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":265,"aSentId":266},{"question":"First of all, what was your feeling when those photographers decided to exact their horrific revenge and lay down their cameras?","answer":"Well, I love the fact that -- that they covered themselves not taking pictures.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":294,"aSentId":295},{"question":"Really?","answer":"It\u0027s not just the Sudan.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":311,"aSentId":312},{"question":"Do they have any rights to privacy when they do that?","answer":"You know, I have no -- I couldn\u0027t really argue for or against that issue.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":329,"aSentId":330},{"question":"Is there some way that a person may be allowed to go out and have dinner with his family or her family without having a camera in the nose of the three year old?","answer":"Having whacked the media, I guess, for that part of it, obviously -- maybe come back to you, George, here.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":356,"aSentId":357},{"question":"So there is the -- I mean, there is a deal with the devil to be struck, isn\u0027t there, when it\u0027s important?","answer":"Well, the -- the -- but the deal is struck long before, you know, I got involved.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":363,"aSentId":364},{"question":"What -- where do you think the line should be drawn here?","answer":"You know, look, I thought that President Obama gave, as he does when -- when he needs to -- he gave one of the greatest speeches I\u0027ve heard in a long, long time.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":391,"aSentId":392},{"question":"It can\u0027t be any worse than being a movie star, can it?","answer":"Really, I mean, honestly, my job is as good as they get.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":409,"aSentId":410},{"question":"I -- do you think he\u0027s better looking than I am?","answer":"No, no.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":422,"aSentId":423},{"question":"Because we see that working so well right now?","answer":"You\u0027ve got to hope, George.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":446,"aSentId":447},{"question":"Is this a half-an-hour show?","answer":"We\u0027re making it a three-parter, now.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":457,"aSentId":458},{"question":"What values do you think they instilled in you as a young -- a young George?","answer":"My father taught me never to mix grain and grape at a very young age.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"But to be serious -- to be serious, what -- what did they teach you?","answer":"Now, listen, you know, I\u0027m very lucky.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":478,"aSentId":479},{"question":"What -- what\u0027s been the proudest you\u0027ve ever been of George and also the least proud?","answer":"Well let\u0027s see, the proudest I have been of George is -- you know, there\u0027s something about -- let me put it this way.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":486,"aSentId":487},{"question":"ORGAN: What\u0027s the naughtiest he\u0027s ever been would you say?","answer":"You know, naughty, yes.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":501,"aSentId":502},{"question":"What was -- what was important to you that when he grew up, he -- he\u0027d adhere to a certain code of behavior as far as you\u0027re concerned?","answer":"You know, Piers, I know what -- I know what you mean here and I\u0027d like to think that I had something to do with both of the kids and how they turned out.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":510,"aSentId":511},{"question":"But if you were to actually take your life to date, if you could replay one moment in your life before you die, what would it be?","answer":"Well, you know, I was thinking about that when you asked the question.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":527,"aSentId":528},{"question":"But it turns out it\u0027s actually this -- I mean you -- you do get malaria flare ups quite regularly, do you?","answer":"No.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":543,"aSentId":544},{"question":"Oh, you wouldn\u0027t swap his life for yours?","answer":"Not at all.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":564,"aSentId":565},{"question":"That\u0027s a great title, is it?","answer":"It\u0027s perfect one.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":576,"aSentId":577},{"question":"George, is he right?","answer":"Exactly.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":594,"aSentId":595},{"question":"Do you think you\u0027ll ever -- will you ever re-marry, George?","answer":"Here we go.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":603,"aSentId":604},{"question":"I\u0027m allowed one, am I?","answer":"-- for the last segment to pull it out.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":606,"aSentId":607},{"question":"Piers, are you married?","answer":"I just got re-married.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":610,"aSentId":611},{"question":"Oh, you did?","answer":"ORGAN: Yeah.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":613,"aSentId":614},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":618,"aSentId":619},{"question":"You could give it all to these people?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t think -- I don\u0027t ever wish I wasn\u0027t super rich.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":626,"aSentId":627},{"question":"Would you tell them that?","answer":"I will.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":654,"aSentId":655},{"question":"Do you think he\u0027s going to run?","answer":"I think he might.","docId":"110121pmt","qSentId":671,"aSentId":672}]